This paper deals with the problem of skyline discovery over categorical attributes in datasets, which is a common problem in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes algorithms that utilize tree data structures and sorted lists, which are common techniques in information retrieval (cs.IR) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses optimization and progressive nature of the proposed algorithms, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
